en 1977 and 1993 — at the Leningrad Maly theater of Opera and ballet.\n\nIn 1987 he graduated from the ballet master faculty of GITIS (teachers — Ekaterina Maximova and Vladimir Vasiliev).\n\nWorking with the music and Russian drama theaters as choreographer and Director.\n\nAssociate Professor of the chair of ballet direction the St. Petersburg Conservatory.\n\nAwards and prizes\n1984 — State prize of the RSFSR behalf of the Vasilyev brothers for the performance of the party modest Alexeevich in the film-ballet \"Anyuta\" (1981)\n2009 — Russian theatre award \"Golden mask\" in the nomination \"Best Director\" for the production of the musical \"the Viper\" (musical Comedy Theatre, Novosibirsk)\nCreativity\nBallet repertoire\nPantaloon, \"the Servant of two masters\" by M. I. Chulaki\nArap, \"Petrushka\" By I. Stravinsky\nDrosselmeyer, The Nutcracker By P. I. Tchaikovsky\nApollon Ableukhov, \"Petersburg\" S. P. Banevich\nThe first performer of parties\n1982 — Spiegelberg, \"the Robbers\" by M. A. Minkova, choreographer N. N. Boyarchikov\n1983 — Host, \"the legend of the bird Donenbay\" Y. A. Simakina on, choreographer Leonid Lebedev\n1984 — the Ugly duckling, \"the Ugly duckling\" by A. A. Petrova, I. V. and A. I. Teslyukevich Mikita\'s, choreographer Leonid Lebedev\nFilmography\n1979 — the Stranger\n1979 — Old tango thief\n1982 — Anya — Modest Alexeitch\n1983 — Mary Poppins, goodbye! sir Louis, the cat\n1983 — I\'m ready for the challenge\n1984 — Pericoli\n1984 — another man\'s wife and husband under the bed — actor in Opera,\n1985 — walk the line — Serge\n1985 — Blue city (film-concert to music by A. Petrov)\n1986 — the Myth\n1987 — Island of lost ships\n1987 — the First meeting, last meeting\n1987 — Chopiniana — the Clown and the Dictator\n1988 — Dangerous man\n1988 — Presumption of innocence\n1988 — These... three winning cards…\n1989 was there Carotene?\n1989 — Cyrano de Bergerac -- entertainer\n1990 — Jokes\n1991 — the Memory of \"Cow March\" — vacationer\n199