10, 1983) — Soviet actor, honored artist of the RSFSR (1953).\n\nBiography\nAnatoliy Abramov was born in the village Nizovoi, Vyatka province, Slobodskoy parish. In 1937 he graduated from the Leningrad theatrical Institute and became an actor of the Leningrad New theater. Then, after serving one year in the red Army, was an actor of Russian theatre of Vyborg and Beloretsky municipal theatre.\n\nFrom 1942 to 1945 Anatoly Abramov participated in the great Patriotic war. Was seconded to the South-Western front as a Lieutenant in January 1943 after the passage of the Riga military infantry school .\n\nFrom 1945 to 1960, Abramov was one of the leading actors of the Leningrad New theater (since 1953 — the Theater. Lensoveta). Then one year, from 1960 to 1961, he worked at the Leningrad theater. Lenin Komsomol.\n\nFrom 1961 to 1975 — actor of the Leningrad Bolshoi drama theater. In 1975 he retired.\n\nDied July 10, 1983.\n\nRewards\nMedal \"For courage\" (26 Sep 1943)\nOrder of the red Star (5 December 1943) — for exemplary performance of command assignments at the front against the German invaders and displaying valor and courage\nOrder of the Patriotic war II degree (24 April 1945) — for exemplary performance of command assignments at the front against the German invaders and displaying valor and courage\nMedal \"For the capture of Konigsberg\" (1945)\nMedal \"For victory over Germany in the great Patriotic war 1941-1945\" (1945)\nHonored artist of the RSFSR (22 Dec 1953)\nMedal \"In commemoration of the 100th anniversary since the birth of Vladimir Ilyich Lenin\" (April 1, 1970)\nCreativity\nTheatre work\nTheatre. Lensoveta\n\n1952 — \"Shadows\" Saltykov-Shchedrin; Director N. P. Akimov — Svistkov\nBolshoi drama theater. Bitter\n\n1959 — the \"barbarians\" Gorky; directed by G. A. Tovstonogov — Dunkin husband\n1972 — \"The Government Inspector\" By N. Gogol; directed by G. A. Tovstonogov — Abdulin\n1974 — \"Energetic people\" by V. M. Shukshin; Director G. A. Tovstonogo